settingDefault.level_one_content:
Level 1 Support

For questions on sign-on access and non-application support, please contact Timeless Hospital.
settingDefault.level_two_content:
Level 2 Support Timeless Medical Systems

The following is list of the various methods of creating a ticket that are available to our Customers. All of these tools are owned by and will be maintained by Supplier.

By Web

  1. Go to the following URL: http://support.timelessmedical.com
  2. Login
  3. Click the IT Help menu item.
  4. Specify the urgency of the issue by choosing one of the listed options.
  5. Input all fields before submitting, and be sure to include your name, hospital or location, contact information, and a detailed explanation of the issue.

Send Milk Home is a new feature in V7 allowing a User to scan bottles/bags against a Mother/Patient to release home. In the event the Patient is still active and that inventory is brought back to Hospital, it can be scanned back through receive (with the original pump date and time). The naming was chosen by the requesting Client, but this feature will allow Formula and collection labels to be scanned to release with Mom/Guardian for a  Patient. Expiration is still tracked so when these expire, the system will alert if a User tries to scan potentially expired bottles previously sent home.
All bottles in home storage are disposed when patient discharged
